I could, of course, laminate more than one list. I could create a rolodex of sticky notes, each filled with the addresses of people I visit on a regular basis. They’d help me remember the million other folks that I sometimes do business with but rarely see.

I figure that I could easily put a laminated list about the size of an envelope between the clipboard and my laptop. Or the desk in front of me. It’s compact and conspicuous; the perfect persistent reminder for those who cram a lot of appointments into a workday. On those days, the net result might be more face-to-face business.

Oh, and laminated sheets. Call 'em the perfect productivity tool. Some U.S. brands have them in various sizes and shapes. It would be easy to create a little laminated consultation lists and keep them within your field-of-view trouble-shooting checklist. Or, to keep. Start small and narrow in one crucial piece of information. Progress to a large, holistic yet information-dense, laminated pad from which to make laser-focused suggestions.

My daily hinge is a slight accidentally, an afterthought. My solution could work for you.
